column1: Population with at least some secondary education (% ages 25 and older)
SDG 4.4 By 2030, substantially increase the number of youth and adults who have relevant skills, including technical and vocational skills, for employment, decent jobs and entrepreneurship
Definition: Percentage of the population ages 25 and older that has reached (but not necessarily completed) a secondary level of education.
Source: UNESCO Institute for Statistics (2020) and Barro and Lee (2018).
